textDisplay: As usual, nice workout! Dean, what I really admire about your instruction is that you actually "instruct". You can find lots of power yoga workouts on YouTube, but the vast majority are lacking in any good instruction. Usually they are done too quickly with no instruction, or the instruction is so minimal it's not useful. I consider myself an advanced intermediate in yoga, but I still want the instructor to guide me through even the most basic of poses. Yoga is like the martial arts - you can spend a lifetime attempting to master the basics. You carefully tell your students how to perform each pose while providing time for the student to recognize what their body is doing and adjust. Thank you for that. Your videos rock!

textDisplay: As usual, nice workout! Dean, what I really admire about your instruction is that you actually "instruct". You can find lots of power yoga workouts on YouTube, but the vast majority are lacking in any good instruction. Usually they are done too quickly with no instruction, or the instruction is so minimal it's not useful. I consider myself an advanced intermediate in yoga, but I still want the instructor to guide me through even the most basic of poses. Yoga is like the martial arts - you can spend a lifetime attempting to master the basics. You carefully tell your students how to perform each pose while providing time for the student to recognize what their body is doing and adjust. Thank you for that. Your videos rock!
